hopobject.body: What do you like doing in your spare time? mighty muggs star wars yoda Researchers have just begun to analyze the data from IRIS, which is known officially as the Interface Region Imaging Spectrograph. The ultimate goal of the mission is to shed light on how this mysterious layer – known as the interface region -- powers the sun’s atmosphere and churns the solar winds that flow through the entire solar system. That could help scientists forecast solar flares and other destructive behaviors that can disrupt and disable satellites, power grids and GPS services.
